<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<html xmlns:MadCap="http://www.madcapsoftware.com/Schemas/MadCap.xsd">
    <body>
        <p>Keep the following in mind when using slideshows:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><span class="SetOffFirstLevel">Print Output </span>Slideshows are not supported in print-based output.<MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Flare"> If you have a topic with a slideshow that will be included in both online and print outputs, you should use condition tags to exclude the sideshow from the print target.</MadCap:conditionalText></li>
            <li><span class="SetOffFirstLevel">Tables and Dynamic HTML </span>You cannot put slideshows within tables or in dynamic HTML elements such as drop-downs and togglers.</li>
        </ul>
    </body>
</html>